---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import site from '../../site.config.json';
const c = site.colours;
const R2 = import.meta.env.PUBLIC_R2_BASE || '';
---
<BaseLayout title="Printix vs Vasion Print -- Cloud Print Management Comparison" description="Compare Printix and Vasion Print for serverless cloud print management. Platform scope, native features, deployment approach, and positioning for Australian organisations.">
  <section class="section-pad">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:860px">
      <div class="hero-split">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">COMPARE</p>
          <h1 style="font-size:clamp(28px,4vw,42px);font-weight:800;margin-bottom:16px">Printix vs Vasion Print</h1>
          <p class="muted" style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.7">Printix and Vasion Print (formerly PrinterLogic) both offer cloud-based, serverless print management designed to eliminate traditional print servers. While both address print server elimination and direct IP printing, they differ significantly in platform scope, deployment flexibility, and how they package functionality. Printix is a dedicated print management platform, while Vasion Print is the print component of a broader automation and document processing platform.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-img-wrap">
          <img src={`${R2}/cloudprinting/cloud-printing-hero-home.jpg`} alt="Cloud print management comparison between Printix and Vasion Print" width="480" height="320" loading="eager" decoding="async" class="hero-img" />
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 style="margin-top:40px;margin-bottom:16px">Printix at a glance</h2>
      <p class="muted" style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">Printix is a dedicated cloud-native print management platform from Tungsten Automation -- focused specifically on print infrastructure, secure release, driver and queue management, and capture workflows. All delivered natively within a single SaaS product. No separate modules, no add-on tiers, no adjacent platform products to evaluate.</p>
      <p class="muted" style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">Print jobs stay on the local network via direct IP printing. A cloud-based driver store automates deployment, often reducing support tickets. Secure print release is built in via the Printix App and Printix Go -- embedded on major MFD brands including Brother, Canon, Epson, FUJIFILM, HP, Konica Minolta, Kyocera, Lexmark, Ricoh, and Xerox. Platform support covers Windows, Mac, Chromebook, iOS, and Android, with identity integration spanning Entra ID, Google Workspace, Okta, and OneLogin.</p>
      <p class="muted" style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">Capture and scanning with OCR to Email, OneDrive, and SharePoint are native features. Pricing is per active user with published entry rates -- billed only for users who log in during the billing cycle.</p>

      <h2 style="margin-top:40px;margin-bottom:16px">Vasion Print at a glance</h2>
      <p class="muted" style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">Vasion Print is the print management component of Vasion's broader cloud-native platform, which also encompasses workflow automation, document processing, and content management capabilities. For print management, Vasion Print emphasises serverless architecture, direct IP printing, centralised management, and secure release functionality.</p>
      <p class="muted" style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">Vasion Print offers deployment flexibility spanning cloud SaaS, on-premise, and hybrid models -- suited to organisations with data sovereignty, air-gapped network, or regulatory requirements. Identity integration includes Entra ID, Okta, and SAML-based providers. Platform support covers Windows, Mac, Chromebook, and Linux.</p>
      <p class="muted" style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">Because Vasion Print sits within a broader platform, organisations evaluating it may find additional capabilities in scanning, digitisation, and workflow automation available through the wider Vasion product suite, depending on configuration and licensing.</p>

      <h2 style="margin-top:40px;margin-bottom:16px">Where each platform is typically preferred</h2>
      <div class="compare-cards">
        <div class="compare-card card-printix">
          <h3 class="card-heading-printix">Printix may suit organisations that</h3>
          <ul class="compare-list list-printix">
            <li>Want a dedicated, focused print management platform with all features included natively in a single SaaS product</li>
            <li>Prioritise streamlined deployment with fewer moving parts, particularly in cloud-first environments</li>
            <li>Prefer transparent per-active-user subscription pricing with published entry rates</li>
            <li>Need native secure print release across 10+ MFD brands via Printix Go</li>
            <li>Require built-in capture and scanning with OCR as a core native feature</li>
            <li>Need iOS and Android mobile device support alongside desktop platforms</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="compare-card card-competitor">
          <h3 class="card-heading-competitor">Vasion Print may suit organisations that</h3>
          <ul class="compare-list list-competitor">
            <li>Want print management as part of a broader workflow automation and document processing platform</li>
            <li>Require on-premise or hybrid deployment options alongside cloud SaaS</li>
            <li>Have data sovereignty or air-gapped network requirements that necessitate local infrastructure</li>
            <li>Need Linux endpoint support in addition to Windows, Mac, and Chromebook</li>
            <li>Prefer to consolidate print, workflow automation, and content management under a single vendor</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mid-cta">
    <div class="container text-center">
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:8px;color:#fff">Choose a focused print solution without added platform complexity</h2>
      <p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.85);margin-bottom:20px;max-width:680px;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto">If your priority is delivering reliable print management through a single, dedicated platform, Printix provides a streamlined approach without requiring broader workflow or automation components. This allows organisations to deploy and manage print infrastructure independently, while retaining the flexibility to integrate with other systems as needed.</p>
      <p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.7);font-size:14px;margin-bottom:20px">Try Printix free for 30 days -- all features included, no credit card required.</p>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:12px;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap">
        <a href={site.hero.ctaPrimaryUrl} class="btn-primary" style="background:#fff;color:#0E7490;font-weight:700">Start free trial</a>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn-secondary" style="border-color:rgba(255,255,255,0.4);color:#fff">Request a quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-pad">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:860px">
      <div class="why-printix">
        <h2 style="margin-bottom:12px">Why organisations choose Printix</h2>
        <p style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">While both platforms address print server elimination, organisations often choose Printix when they prioritise a dedicated, cloud-native print management platform with native functionality and simplified deployment, rather than evaluating print management as one component within a broader platform suite.</p>
        <p style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">Printix provides key capabilities such as secure print release across 10+ MFD brands, automated driver management, cross-platform support, and capture with OCR as native features within one SaaS application. Vasion Print delivers print management as part of a broader platform that also addresses workflow automation and document processing, which may involve evaluating additional components depending on organisational requirements.</p>
        <p style="line-height:1.7">This distinction can influence deployment complexity, ongoing administration, and how features are packaged and licensed across environments.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="break-img-wrap">
        <img src={`${R2}/cloudprinting/printx-cloud-printing-home-hero.jpg`} alt="Printix cloud print management platform in a modern office environment" width="860" height="400" loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="break-img" />
      </div>

      <h2 style="margin-top:40px;margin-bottom:16px">Key considerations</h2>
      <p class="muted" style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">The most significant difference between these platforms is scope and focus. Printix is a dedicated print management product delivering all capabilities through a single SaaS application. Vasion Print is the print management component of a broader platform that also addresses workflow automation and document processing. Organisations should consider whether they need a focused print solution with native features or a broader platform that includes print management alongside other capabilities.</p>
      <p class="muted" style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">Deployment models also differ. Printix is cloud SaaS only, which often simplifies operations in cloud-first environments. Vasion Print offers cloud, on-premise, and hybrid deployment, providing flexibility for environments with specific infrastructure or compliance constraints.</p>
      <p class="muted" style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">Pricing models differ and should be confirmed directly with each vendor. Printix publishes per-active-user subscription pricing with all features included. Vasion Print typically uses enterprise or quote-based pricing that may vary depending on platform scope, deployment model, and organisational requirements.</p>

      <p class="muted compare-disclaimer" style="font-size:13px;margin-top:32px;font-style:italic">This comparison is based on publicly available information and general product positioning. Features and capabilities may vary depending on configuration, licensing, and deployment. Verify current details directly with each vendor before making purchasing decisions.</p>
      <p class="muted compare-disclaimer" style="font-size:13px;margin-top:12px;font-style:italic">Vasion and Vasion Print are trademarks of their respective owner. This site is not affiliated with or endorsed by Vasion. Printix is a product of Tungsten Automation.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-pad section-dark" style="padding:60px 0">
    <div class="container text-center">
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:12px">Try Printix free for 30 days</h2>
      <p class="muted" style="margin-bottom:24px">All features included. No credit card required.</p>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:12px;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap"><a href={site.hero.ctaPrimaryUrl} class="btn-primary">Start free trial</a><a href="/contact" class="btn-secondary" style="border-color:rgba(255,255,255,0.3);color:#fff">Request a quote</a></div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <style is:inline>
    .eyebrow{font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:var(--brand);letter-spacing:0.06em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:12px}
    .hero-split{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:40px;align-items:center;margin-bottom:0}
    .hero-img-wrap{border-radius:12px;overflow:hidden}
    .hero-img{width:100%;height:auto;border-radius:12px;object-fit:cover}
    .break-img-wrap{margin:40px 0;border-radius:12px;overflow:hidden}
    .break-img{width:100%;height:auto;border-radius:12px;object-fit:cover}
    .compare-cards{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:24px;margin-top:24px}
    .card-printix{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#0891B2 0%,#0E7490 100%);border-radius:12px;padding:28px;color:#fff}
    .card-competitor{background:var(--neutral);border-radius:12px;padding:28px}
    .card-heading-printix{font-size:18px;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:12px;color:#fff}
    .card-heading-competitor{font-size:18px;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:12px;color:var(--muted)}
    .compare-list{list-style:none;padding:0}
    .compare-list li{position:relative;padding-left:20px;font-size:15px;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:8px}
    .list-printix li{color:rgba(255,255,255,0.92)}
    .list-printix li::before{content:'\2713';position:absolute;left:0;color:#22D3EE;font-weight:700}
    .list-competitor li{color:var(--muted)}
    .list-competitor li::before{content:'\2713';position:absolute;left:0;color:var(--muted);font-weight:700}
    .why-printix{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#ECFEFF 0%,#F0FDFA 100%);border-radius:16px;padding:32px;border:1px solid #A5F3FC}
    .why-printix h2{color:#0E7490}
    .why-printix p{color:#115E59;margin:0}
    .why-printix p+p{margin-top:12px}
    .mid-cta{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#0891B2 0%,#0E7490 100%);padding:48px 0;margin:0}
    .mid-cta h2{font-size:clamp(22px,3vw,30px)}
    @media(max-width:768px){.compare-cards{grid-template-columns:1fr}.hero-split{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
